metadata.doc: How to create a category? | Dukaan® Help CenterGo to DukaanGo to DukaanAll CollectionsProductsHow to create a category?How to create a category?Learn how to add categories to your storeNWritten by Namrata Sawhney Updated over a week agoCategorizing all your products can be helpful by organizing products in your store.First of all, head over to the Products section and click on Categories. To add a new category, click on Add new category button. You'll see the below screen. Enter the name of the category and select a category picture that you want to showcase. Click on Add Category button to save the category to your store. Once added, you can add products to this category. Note that if you select your Business Category as Restaurants & Hotels, you will see another option while adding a category. You can choose to show this category to dining customers, delivery customers, or both. metadata.title: How to use Store Banners? | Dukaan® Help Center
metadata.doc: How to use Store Banners? | Dukaan® Help CenterGo to DukaanGo to DukaanAll CollectionsMobileHow to use Store Banners?How to use Store Banners?Learn how to use Promo Banners on AppNWritten by Namrata Sawhney Updated over a week agoNow, you don’t need to know complex graphic designing tools to create banners and marketing designs to promote your business. We have made beautifully designed store banners for your online business that are pre-built & customizable to suit your needs.  These banners can be used on different occasions, for example, when you’re running sales events during festivals, promotional events during special days like Mother’s Day, Father’s Day, or promoting a new product.  To choose a banner of your choice, click on Manage. Now choose Promotional Designs and then select Store Banners. There are two types of designs available for your use - Editable and Non-editable. With editable designs, you can change the edit heading, description, and footer on the designs to suit your needs. Non-editable as the name suggests, can’t be edited much and you can only edit footers on the banners. Select any design that you like and click on Edit text and change it as per your needs.  When you’re finished making changes, click on the Save button. Once done, click on the Share button to share these banners on Facebook, Instagram, Telegram, or any other social media platform to promote your business.Did this answer your question?😞😐😃Dukaan® for PCPrivacy PolicyAbout Dukaan®FacebookTwitterLinkedInIntercomWe run on Intercom

metadata.title: How to use Store Timings? | Dukaan® Help Center
metadata.doc: How to use Store Timings? | Dukaan® Help CenterGo to DukaanGo to DukaanAll CollectionsStore ProfileHow to use Store Timings?How to use Store Timings?Learn how to set automatic working hours for your Dukaan storeNWritten by Namrata Sawhney Updated over a week agoNote: This is applicable only to users in India. Store Timings allow you to manage your store's working hours on Dukaan. This feature comes in handy when you want to set specific opening and closing times so that you don't have to manually do it every time. To get started with this, go to Manage and click on Store Timings. You'll see the below screen. Here, you can set store opening and closing times for all days.  If you want to keep your store open for 24 hours, let the option as is. If you want to set a specific time against every day, click on 24 hours. Now from the drop-down, choose the opening time and then the closing time, as illustrated below. You can do it for the rest of the day, by following the steps mentioned above. Once done, your store will turn Online and Offline at the selected time.   If your business is OFF once a day every week, you can turn the store Offline for that day. Once done, your store will remain Offline for that day every week in the future unless you change it. Once you've set the timings for the store, click on Save and the new store timings will be applied to your store.Did this answer your question?😞😐😃Dukaan® for PCPrivacy PolicyAbout Dukaan®FacebookTwitterLinkedInIntercomWe run on Intercom

metadata.title: How to use WhatsApp Stories? | Dukaan® Help Center
metadata.doc: How to use WhatsApp Stories? | Dukaan® Help CenterHow to use WhatsApp Stories?Learn how to use WhatsApp Stories Designs to promote your businessNWritten by Namrata Sawhney Updated over a week agoTo help you promote your business, we have designed beautiful promotional images which can be shared on your WhatsApp Stories. As WhatsApp is used by a lot of people, you have a higher chance of getting orders from people who already trust you and your business, when you share it.  Note: Learn how to edit and design your own WhatsApp Stories. To choose a banner of your choice, click on Manage. Now choose Promotional Designs and then select WhatsApp Stories. There are two types of designs available for your use - Editable and Non-editable. With editable designs, you can change the text on the designs to suit your needs. Non-editable as the name suggests, can’t be edited, and should be used as is. To begin, click on the Editable button to filter out designs that can be edited. Select any design that you like. To edit the text, double-click on the text and change it as per your needs.  If you want to use other designs, click on the Non-editable button and choose the WhatsApp Story of your choice. Please note, these designs can’t be edited. Once done, click on the Download this story button at the bottom. Now, you can use these designs as your WhatsApp Story and promote your business.Did this answer your question?😞😐😃

Customers can pay the order amount by clicking on the Pay Online button. metadata.doc: How to add size and color options to products? | Dukaan® Help CenterGo to DukaanGo to DukaanAll CollectionsProductsHow to add size and color options to products?How to add size and color options to products?Learn how to add multiple sizes or colors to your productsNWritten by Namrata Sawhney Updated over a week agoIf your product has variants and you want to add Size or Color, Click on Add Variants at the bottom while adding a new product or editing the details for a product. To add Size, click on Add Size button. Enter size name, its MRP, and selling price. If you want to delete any size, click on the Delete button to remove it.  If the product has different color options, click on Add Color and select the preferred color from the colors shown.  If the color is not matching with the product, click on Custom to select the desired color according to the product.  Once done, click on Save and continue button at the bottom. metadata.title: How do Online Payments Settlements work? | Dukaan® Help Center
metadata.doc: hold tells you the total amount that has not been credited to your linked account. For the amount to be credited to your account, deliver the orders to the customers.  • Once you deliver the order to the customer, the amount will be credited to your bank account. We process the payouts three times a day i.e. at 11 AM, 4 PM & 9 PM.    How to check the status of your payments? To check the status of online payments against your orders, go to Manage then click on Online Payments. You can filter the status of the payment by - On hold, Payouts, and Refunds •On hold - It shows all amounts that customers have already paid but have not been credited to your account. This will be credited once you deliver the order. • Payouts - It shows all the payments that have been credited to your bank account. •Refunds - Amount that has been refunded back to your customer when you rejected the order.  Note: If your amount is still on hold, please reach out to us at support@mydukaan.ioPayouts will be released only on working days ( weekends & public holidays are excluded).Read MoreHow to use online payments for your store?How to do KYC to increase the payment limit?How to use the payment link to accept online payment on COD orders?Did this answer your question?😞😐😃Dukaan® for PCPrivacy PolicyAbout Dukaan®FacebookTwitterLinkedInIntercomWe run on Intercom
